<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-12-1177 </DOCNO><TEXT>The study 'Nuclear energy' includes the history of nuclear energy, thephysical basis of nuclear energy use, nuclear weapons, nuclear reactors,the biological effects of ionising radiation, nuclear irradiation ofhuman beings (natural, due to civilisation), environmental loading bynuclear powerstations, accident and incidents, the fuel cycle, the atomicwaste problem and alternatives to nuclear energy. The study is intendedfor science and social science teachers.</TEXT></DOC>